## 1. SEMANTIC HTML STRUCTURE

### üö´ STRICTLY FORBIDDEN (The "Anti-Div Soup" Rule)

**Never use `<div>` when a semantic element exists:**
```tsx
// ‚ùå WRONG - Generic div soup
<div className="article-wrapper">
  <div className="article-header">
    <div className="title">Parkinson's Disease</div>
  </div>
  <div className="content">
    <div className="section">
      <div className="section-title">Symptoms</div>
      <div className="text">...</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

// ‚úÖ CORRECT - Semantic HTML5
<article className="article-wrapper">
  <header className="article-header">
    <h1>Parkinson's Disease</h1>
  </header>
  <section className="content">
    <h2>Symptoms</h2>
    <p>...</p>
  </section>
</article>
```

### ‚úÖ MANDATED SEMANTIC TAGS

Use these tags based on content purpose:

| Tag | Purpose | Example Use Case |
|-----|---------|------------------|
| `<article>` | Self-contained content | Wiki article pages, blog posts |
| `<section>` | Thematic grouping | Symptoms section, Treatment section |
| `<aside>` | Tangentially related | Clinical pearls, related articles sidebar |
| `<nav>` | Navigation links | Main menu, breadcrumbs, pagination |
| `<header>` | Introductory content | Page title, article metadata |
| `<footer>` | Closing content | References, last updated date |
| `<main>` | Primary content | Wraps the main article content (one per page) |
| `<figure>` + `<figcaption>` | Images with captions | Anatomy diagrams, MRI scans |

### üìê HEADING HIERARCHY RULES

**Strict enforcement:**

1. **One `<h1>` per page** (the article title or page title)
2. **Logical nesting:** Never skip levels (h1 ‚Üí h3 is forbidden)
3. **Hierarchy reflects structure:** Subtopics under main topics
```tsx
// ‚ùå WRONG - Broken hierarchy
<h1>Stroke Management</h1>
<h3>Acute Phase</h3>  {/* Skipped h2! */}
<h2>Recovery</h2>     {/* Out of order! */}

// ‚úÖ CORRECT - Logical hierarchy
<h1>Stroke Management</h1>
<h2>Acute Phase</h2>
  <h3>Thrombolysis</h3>
  <h3>Thrombectomy</h3>
<h2>Recovery Phase</h2>
  <h3>Physical Therapy</h3>
```

### üîç SEMANTIC VALIDATION CHECKLIST

Before committing, verify:
- [ ] No `<div>` used where `<section>`, `<article>`, or `<aside>` would be appropriate
- [ ] All navigation wrapped in `<nav>`
- [ ] Images in context use `<figure>` + `<figcaption>`
- [ ] Only one `<h1>` exists on the page
- [ ] Headings follow logical order (no skipped levels)

